            <h3>Safety Guidelines- Skill Sharing</h3>						
            <p>We at Sharingdais believe that skills can be learnt from anyone of any age, gender and profession by anyone of any age, gender and profession. These are the basic community guideline for teachers and students to be followed for using the Skill Sharing category.</p>                          
            <h2>Do’s-</h2>                      
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Mutual Respect </strong></li>
                <li>Since there are real people involved behind each profile and listing on Sharingdais.com, mutual respect in interacting with each other is expected from the community</li>
                <li><strong>Respect Copyright</strong> </li>
                <li>Please use content for which you are the creator or hold the copyright for</li>                      
                <li><strong>Get Proactive</strong></li>
                <li>Be proactive in discussing the issues for clarification of things taught in the classes</li>
                <li><strong>Be Courteous in interactions</strong></li>
                <li>Please provide feedback to improve the teacher’s performance. Please don’t attack each other during feedback session, instead be constructive in criticism</li>
                <li><strong>Pursue Lifelong Learning</strong></li>                      
                <li>We will be hosting skill sharing for a whole lot of categories. Learn as much as you can</li>
            </ol>
